        <b>The following companies have confirmed their
        attendance.</b>
        <br />
        <br />
        <strong>Accenture</strong>
        <br />
        <a href="http://www.accenture.ca/"
             rel="external">http://www.accenture.ca/</a>
        <br />
        Accenture is a global management consulting, technology 
	services and outsourcing company. Committed to delivering 
	innovation, Accenture collaborates with its clients to help 
	them become high-performance businesses and governments. 
	With deep industry and business process expertise, broad 
	global resources and a proven track record, Accenture can 
	mobilize the right people, skills, and technologies to help 
	clients improve their performance.  With approximately 
	140,000 people in 48 countries, the company generated net 
	revenues of US$16.65 billion for the fiscal year ended Aug. 31, 
	2006. To learn more about careers at Accenture, visit www.accenture.ca/careers.
        <br />
        <br />
        
        <strong>Apparent Networks
        <br /></strong><a href="http://www.apparentnetworks.com"
             rel="external">http://www.apparentnetworks.com/</a>
        <br />
	Apparent Networks is the developer of AppCritical [formerly known as AppareNet], a software application that provides a radically different and superior basis for assessing, measuring and diagnosing converged networks to facilitate the optimal performance and management of data, VoIP and video applications.

<p>Utilizing a patent-protected expert technology for network behavior, Apparent Networks' AppCritical software provides network diagnostic, assessment, measurement and monitoring functionality that has proven vastly superior to that provided by the traditional network management products.</p>	

        <br />
        <br />

        <strong>Atimi Software
        <br /></strong><a href="http://www.atimi.com"
             rel="external">http://www.atimi.com/</a>
        <br />
	"While the software industry continues to grow, more and more new businesses emerge to compete for very attractive markets. History has shown us that whoever wins the customer, wins the market. In most cases, it's the companies which differentiate themselves and gain a competitive advantage that succeed.

<p>It's our mission to help our clients win their customers through delivering software development on time. By helping our clients hit their launch dates more reliably than their competitors, they will be in a stronger position to earn the trust of their customers and give them a better chance at dominating the market."</p>

        <br />
        <br />


        <strong>BC Hydro
        <br /></strong><a href="http://www.bchydro.com"
             rel="external">http://www.bchydro.com/</a>
        <br />
	One of the largest electric utilities in Canada, BC Hydro's vision is to provide Reliable Power, at Low Cost, for Generations.  Currently, BC Hydro serves more than 1.6 million customers, 94% of BC's population 
with a 99.96% reliability rate. 
BC Hydro has a wide variety of opportunities available for students and graduates! We hire Co-op Students, Power Smart Representatives, Engineers-in-Training, Managers and Professionals in Development, Graduate Technologists-in-Training and Apprentices on an ongoing basis. Check out what BC Hydro has to offer you today!
        <br />
        <br />


        <strong>Business Objects</strong>
        <br />
        <a href="http://www.businessobjects.com/"
             rel="external">http://www.businessobjects.com/</a>
        <br />
        With more than 37,000 customers worldwide, Business Objects helps organizations gain better insight into their business, improve decision making, and optimize enterprise performance. We provide the only business intelligence (BI) platform that delivers a complete set of BI capabilities. Our supportive culture helps you build your skills and expertise through exposure to transnational projects and opportunities, a team of some of the brightest minds in the industry, and a focus on learning and development. You provide the passion and direction, and we'll give you the support and opportunity you need to evolve your career. 

<p>Agnes Zielichowska
<br>Campus Recruitment Coordinator
<br>Tel: (604) 647-8063</p>
        <br />
        <br />

        <strong>Certified Management Accountants of BC
        <br /></strong><a href="http://www.cmabc.com/"
             rel="external">http://www.cmabc.com/
        <br /></a>
	The CMA designation opens the door to a competitive income, a broad range of career opportunities and exciting workplace challenges. CMAs provide employers with the ideal balance of three essential and interdependent business disciplines: management, accounting, and strategy. This powerful combination of skills defines the CMA.s unique value to an organization as they are able to apply contemporary and emerging best business practices to a wide array of business functions.  With nearly 40,000 members worldwide, CMAs provide an integrating perspective to business decision-making, applying best management practices in information technology, finance, and operations to help grow successful businesses.
        <br />
        <br />

        <strong>Counterpath
        <br /></strong><a href="http://www.counterpath.com/"
             rel="external">http://www.counterpath.com/
        <br /></a>
	CounterPath Solutions is a developer of award-winning, carrier-grade SIP soft phones for the telecom industry. Combining VoIP, Video over IP and Instant Messaging with Presence, our software application suite powers the VoIP solutions of some of the world.s largest service providers and equipment manufacturers including Cisco, Lucent, AT&T, British Telecom and Deutsche Telecom. With over 210 customers in more than 50 countries, our technology is deployed in more than 6,000,000 endpoints

worldwide.  

<p>Join the VoIP revolution:  hr@counterpath.com</p>
        <br />
        <br />

	        <strong>Electronic Arts Canada
        <br /></strong><a href="http://www.eacanada.com/"
             rel="external">http://www.eacanada.com/
        <br /></a>
	Electronic Arts Canada (EAC) is the world's largest development studio for interactive entertainment. EAC develops and produces video games for the PlayStation(r)2 and PlayStation(r)3 computer entertainment system and PSP(tm) handheld entertainment system from Sony; the Xbox(tm) 360 
video game console and Xbox from Microsoft; and the Nintendo 
GameCube(tm), Wii, DS and Game Boy(r) Advance, as well as the PC. 
As the world's number one developer and publisher of interactive entertainment, EA is the leader in one of the world's fastest-growing industries. EAC provides a uniquely stimulating work culture and an environment that is geared toward creative expression.
        <br />
        <br />

	        <strong>EQO
        <br /></strong><a href="http://www.eqo.com/"
